President Joe Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris held a meeting with a bipartisan group of Members of Congress in the Oval Office to discuss the need for investment in infrastructure. They shared their vision outlined in the American Jobs Plan, which aims to create jobs, rebuild infrastructure, and ensure the United States remains competitive with China. The President asked for feedback and follow-up on the proposals discussed, emphasizing that inaction is not an option. The meeting included representatives from Congressional committees responsible for infrastructure and transportation. The President intends to continue engaging with Congress and stakeholders on this issue.